items.example: Total dollar sales of the selected product over the date range and across all selected stores. This is net of promotional discounts but does not reflect manufacturer coupons or rebates.

example: Total dollar sales of the selected product over the date range and across all selected stores. This is net of promotional discounts but does not reflect manufacturer coupons or rebates.
Total unit sales of the selected product over the date range and across all selected stores. For random weight items each purchase is counted as one unit regardless of weight.
Total number of baskets seen over the date range and across all selected stores.
Number of stores selling at least one unit of the selected product in the date range. This indicates if distribution changed, or may reflect store openings or closures.
Average number of units of the selected product in a basket (among baskets with at least one unit of the selected product).
Average dollars of the selected product in a basket (among baskets with at least one unit of the selected product).

Unit sales on a per store per week basis. This is calculated by taking the total unit sales for the item divided by (the number of stores X number of weeks). It includes promoted and non-promoted sales. This measure is often used as input to replenishment systems.
Sales $ on a per store per week basis. This is calculated by taking the total Sales $ for the item/(the number of stores x the number of weeks). It includes both promoted and non-promoted sales.
Average price per unit for the selected products in the date range. If product is a random weight item this is on a per purchase basis, not per unit of measure.
